Date: Fri, 5 Feb 2016 14:35:53 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] drm/radeon: hold reference to fences in radeon_sa_bo_new
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: f6ff4f67cdf8455d0a4226eeeaf5af17c37d05eb
Patch-mainline: 4.5-rc4
References: boo#955096,boo#967938

An arbitrary amount of time can pass between spin_unlock and
radeon_fence_wait_any, so we need to ensure that nobody frees the
fences from under us.

Based on the analogous fix for amdgpu.

Signed-off-by: Nicolai Hähnle <nicolai.haehnle@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Christian König <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
